body:
### Description

I have a project where I'm colorizing mesh data using Canvas.DrawVertices. Passing in a color array works fine in v2.88.9 but after updating to 3.116.1 the output is simply black.

The code block below was pulled from the samples project with some setup/export lines added by me to represent how I'm using it. My project targets .NET 8.

### Code

```cs
// Setting up basic canvas
var imageInfo = new SKImageInfo(
    width: 200,
    height: 200,
    colorType: SKColorType.Rgba8888,
    alphaType: SKAlphaType.Premul);

var surface = SKSurface.Create(imageInfo);

// Code copied from Samples
surface.Canvas.Clear(SKColors.White);
var paint = new SKPaint
{
    IsAntialias = true
};

var vertices = new[] { new SKPoint(110, 20), new SKPoint(160, 200), new SKPoint(10, 200) };
var colors = new[] { SKColors.Red, SKColors.Green, SKColors.Blue };

surface.Canvas.DrawVertices(SKVertexMode.Triangles, vertices, colors, paint);


// Encode the result as a png
using var data = surface.Snapshot();
using var pngImage = data.Encode(SKEncodedImageFormat.Png, 100);

// Save the png to a stream
using var fileStream = File.Create(filePath);
pngImage.SaveTo(fileStream);
```

### Expected Behavior

Expected behavior is a gradient triangle (output when run in version 2.88.9):

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/afa656d4-1966-496c-be0f-50d3d325f554)

### Actual Behavior

Actual behavior is a black triangle (output when run in version 3.116.1):

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5a9f1421-92d4-49f6-8f65-e7fb990cb82f)

### Version of SkiaSharp

3.116.0 (Current)

### Last Known Good Version of SkiaSharp

2.88.9 (Previous)

### IDE / Editor

Visual Studio (Windows)

